## VI. THE DICHOTOMY RESTATED: EXTERNAL EXPANSION VS. INTRINSIC DEEPENING

We can now state the core dichotomy with formal precision:

| Dimension | Silicon Scaling | Carbon Scaling (IISL) |
|---|---|---|
| **Primary variable** | E (energy/compute) | B × C (integration × coherence) |
| **Scaling curve** | Quadratic energy cost | Linear energy cost |
| **Coherence ceiling** | Structural (low Φ by architecture) | None (Φ-maximizing substrate) |
| **Consciousness status** | Provably uncertain | Provably present |
| **Alignment mechanism** | External (RLHF, safety training) | Intrinsic (embodied values, survival) |
| **Thermodynamic regime** | Approaching wall | Optimization-governed |
| **Failure mode** | Misalignment, energy collapse | Ethical evolution required |

The silicon path solves the *quantity* of intelligence. The carbon path solves the *quality and reliability* of intelligence. These are not the same problem, and conflating them is the foundational error of the current technological moment.

