## IX. TESTABLE HYPOTHESES

A theory without falsifiable predictions is a philosophy. The IISL generates the following experimentally testable claims:

**H1 — Neuroplasticity:** CRISPRa upregulation of BDNF and synaptic density genes in adult mammalian models will produce measurable increases in learning rate and working memory capacity compared to controls.

**H2 — Sensory Integration:** Reactivation of dormant UVS opsin genes in adult human stem cell-derived retinal organoids will produce functional UV-responsive photoreceptors.

**H3 — Radiation Hardening:** Stable somatic integration of tardigrade Dsup via AAV vector in human cell lines will produce a statistically significant reduction in double-strand DNA breaks following ionizing radiation exposure.

**H4 — Coherence Scaling:** Subjects with epigenetically enhanced prefrontal-sensory connectivity will show measurably higher Φ proxy scores (perturbational complexity index) than baseline controls on EEG/TMS paradigms.

**H5 — IISL Ratio:** Across a sample of artificially enhanced biological systems versus comparable silicon systems performing equivalent cognitive tasks, the carbon-based systems will demonstrate superior I per unit E — i.e., more intelligence per watt.

