## X. CONCLUSION: THE REAL COMPETITION

The question being asked in every major AI laboratory on Earth right now is: *how do we scale intelligence?* The answer everyone is pursuing is: more compute, more energy, more parameters.

This paper argues that this answer is correct for silicon and wrong as a universal law. Intelligence, properly defined — as the capacity to perceive, integrate, reason, and act in alignment with coherent internal goals — scales differently in different substrates. In carbon-based biological systems, it scales with integration and coherence per unit of thermodynamic cost.

By late 2025, AI labs were already rethinking scaling strategies as diminishing returns set in and investor enthusiasm cooled around the promise of exponential intelligence growth. [HEC Paris](https://www.hec.edu/en/dare/tech-ai/ai-beyond-scaling-laws) The silicon wall is not a future risk. It is arriving now.

The carbon path is not a backup plan. It is a competing scaling law — one that has been running for 600 million years of neural evolution, and one that has already produced the only substrate in the known universe confirmed to be conscious, goal-directed, and self-modifying.

The future of intelligence will not be decided by who computes faster.

**It will be decided by who remains coherent under scale.**

